id: pm-bav0
title: Package scaffold emits least-privilege manifest policy metadata
description: "New package and extension scaffolds should teach package authors the same least-privilege manifest contract as first-party packages: trusted=true, sandbox_profile=strict for pure starter commands, and explicit false permissions. This keeps generated packages compatible with extension policy enforcement and makes the SDK/package author baseline easier to copy."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:packages","area:sdk"
created_at: "2026-06-21T08:27:34.890Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-21T08:47:11.094Z"
author: codex-impl
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: Implemented least-privilege policy metadata in the scaffold manifest generator and documented the generated contract.
expected_result: "New package and extension scaffolds declare trusted=true, sandbox_profile=strict, and explicit false permissions, with tests and docs proving the baseline for package authors."
actual_result: Generated scaffolds now emit the least-privilege manifest metadata; focused tests assert package and extension manifests; SDK and extension docs explain how to keep or relax the policy metadata.
